    PW_GAUGE2[ STATE,TITLE$,PCT$,UNITS1,UNITS2,POS1,POS2,GSCREEN ]    
    @{u}                                                              @{uu}


    ----------
    Parameters
    ----------

    STATE : State of the requester

        STATE = 0 : Opening of the requester
        STATE = 1 : Updating of the requester
        STATE = 2 : Closing of the requester

    TITLE$ : Text to display in title (less than 68 characters)

    PCT$ : Text to display before the evolution percentage of gauge n°1

    UNITS1 : Total number of units for the gauge n°1

    UNITS2 : Total number of units for the gauge n°2

    POS1 : Position of the gauge n°1 (between 0 [0%] and UNITS [100%])

    POS2 : Position of the gauge n°2 (between 0 [0%] and UNITS [100%])

    GSCREEN : Number of the screen for the requester
       
    
    ------
    Result
    ------
    
    None.
       

    -----------------------
    Other Procedures Needed
    -----------------------

        @{" PW_FRAME2           " LINK "PW_FRAME2"      }
        @{" PW_ALIGN            " LINK "PW_ALIGN"       }
        @{" PW_HSLIDER          " LINK "PW_HSLIDER"     }
        @{" PW_ENT              " LINK "PW_ENT"         }
@ENDNODE


@NODE PW_STAR "PW_Star"
@TOC "PROCEDURES"

    @{u}                                                  @{uu}
    
    PW_STAR [ XC,YC,NEDGES,RAD1,RAD2,STATE,CLR0,CLR1 ]
    @{u}                                                  @{uu}


    ----------
    Parameters
    ----------

    XC : x-coordinate of the star center

    YC : y-coordinate of the star center
        
    NEDGES : Number of edges for the star

        NEDGES >= 3

    RAD1 : Lenght of the internal radius of the star

    RAD2 : Lenght of the external radius of the star

    STATE : State of the star (only valid with odd number of edges)

        STATE = 0 : Point above

        STATE = 1 : Point below
    
    CLR0 : Border color of the star

        CLR0 >= 0 : Use color n°CLR0
        CLR0 <  0 : Use color PW_BLACK
    
    CLR1 : Filling color of the star

        CLR1 >= 0 : Use color n°CLR1
        CLR1 <  0 : No filling
       
    
    ------
    Result
    ------
    
    None.
       

    ------------------------
    Others procedures needed
    ------------------------

        @{" PW_ENT              " LINK "PW_ENT"         }
@ENDNODE


